						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Broken slab near the ruined Mallikārjuna temple on the bank of the Bhīmarathi river.</hi></p>						

						<p>Sōvidēva—(A.D. 1172).</p>						

						<p>This record is dated in the king's regnal <hi rend="bold">year 4, Khara, Phālguṇa, Amāvāsye, Monday.</hi> The details of the date correspond to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1172, February 25,</hi> which was Friday and not Monday as stated in the record.</p>						

						<p>The inscription registers a gift of land for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of god Kūḍaladēva, by Dhāyya, Māya-sāhaṇi, Rēchagāvuṇḍa and others.</p>						

						</summary>
